Maura Anish Homework 3 Dashboard

Introduction

This dashboard is being constructed for DACSS 690V: Data Visualization, a course taught by Dr. Jose Manuel Magallanes Reyes in the Winter 2025 session at the University of Massachusetts Amherst. As of January 21, 2025, this dashboard contains three plots: 1) a boxplot of student-teacher ratios at K-12 schools in Washington, which refers to Heckmann (2024) for additional context, 2) a side-by-side boxplot of crimes committed in Massachusetts, according to the age of the perpetrator, and 3) a map of Boston with information about political donations made in 2024.

References

Heckmann, Corinne. 2024. “Ratio of Students to Teaching Staff by Type of Institution.” OECD: OECD Data Explorer. https://data-explorer.oecd.org/vis?lc=en&df[ds]=dsDisseminateFinalDMZ&df[id]=DSD_EAG_UOE_NON_FIN_PERS@DF_UOE_NF_PERS_STR&df[ag]=OECD.EDU.IMEP.
